text: Tropical Storm Gordon was a tropical cyclone in early September 2018. The storm developed on September 1, 2018. Gordon crossed over southern Florida near Key Largo and Miami on September 3, 2018. The storm went into the Gulf of Mexico later that day. Tropical storm and hurricane warnings were put in effect from southeast Louisiana to the Florida Panhandle. Gordon was expected to become a hurricane before moving onto the United States Gulf Coast. ==References== Category:Hurricanes in the United States Category:2018 in the United States Category:2018 Atlantic hurricane season Category:Atlantic tropical storms Category:Hurricanes in Mississippi
